<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="385" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1446,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1446,1471]" pageId="3" pageNumber="385">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Gena broad, as wide as first flagellomere. Posterior 1/2 of ocellar triangle shining yellow, with a short rhombate black macula, anterior 1/2 extremely narrow, linear, extending to anterior margin of frons. Surstylus broadly elongate, slightly parallel–sided, with small spinous processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="386" pageId="3" pageNumber="385" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1446,2011]" box="[199,998,1554,1579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1554,1579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="385">Description</emphasis>
. Male. Body length 3.0– 
<quantity box="[618,704,1555,1579]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="385" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[856,994,1555,1579]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="385" unit="mm" value="2.15" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="2.1">2.1–2.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1446,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="385">Head yellow with gray microtomentum, 0.8x as long as high; face somewhat concave in lateral view, facial carina indistinct; frons 0.9x as long as wide, projecting only slightly in front of eye; gena broad, as wide as first flagellomere; parafacial narrow. Ocellar triangle occupying 1/3 of posterior width of frons, posterior 1/2 of ocellar triangle shining yellow, with a short rhombate black macula, anterior 1/2 extremely narrow, linear, extending to anterior margin of frons; ocellar tubercle light brown. Occiput yellow except for brown middle 1/3. Clypeus light yellowish orange. Cephalic setae and setulae black. Antenna yellow with thick grayish microtomentum except for brown dorsal 1/2 of first flagellomere; first flagellomere as wide as long; arista black with short black setulae. Proboscis brownish with yellow setulae; palpus yellow with yellow setulae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1446,2011]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,896]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="386" pageId="3" pageNumber="385">
Thorax yellow with gray microtomentum. Postpronotum with a brown spot. Scutum as long as wide, with 5 black longitudinal stripes, medial stripe slightly broad and extending to posterior 3/4 of scutum; basal 2/3 of lateral stripe narrow, brown; sublateral stripe short and narrow. Thoracic pleuron shiny yellow without microtomentum except for brown paratergite; black anteroventral portions of anepisternum, anterior portion of anepimeron, ventral 1/2 of katepisternum and posteroventral portion of katepimeron. Postnotum black. Scutellum yellow except for yellowish brown lateral margins, 0.6x as long as wide; 
<emphasis box="[764,821,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">ap sc</emphasis>
developed, as long as scutellum; 
<emphasis box="[1196,1264,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">sap sc</emphasis>
0.5x as long as scutellum. Setae and setulae on thorax black, developed; 
<emphasis box="[795,831,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">npl</emphasis>
1+2, 
<emphasis box="[896,954,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">a npl</emphasis>
as long as 
<emphasis box="[1080,1137,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">p npl</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[1152,1202,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">a pa</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1257,1306,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">p pa</emphasis>
developed, 
<emphasis box="[151,200,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">a pa</emphasis>
<date box="[208,236,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">2x</date>
as long as 
<emphasis box="[362,412,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">p pa</emphasis>
; 1 
<emphasis box="[449,475,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">dc</emphasis>
, 
<date box="[490,517,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">2x</date>
as long as 
<emphasis box="[644,694,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">a pa</emphasis>
. Legs yellow except for brown basal portion of hind femur, distal 3/5 of fore tibia, mid tibia, middle portion of hind tibia, fore and mid tarsi and hind tarsomere 5. Setulae on legs black. Mid tibia with a distinct black apical spur, which is as long as diameter of tibia. Wing 2.6x as long as wide, hyaline; veins brown. Proportions of costal sectors 2–4 is the ratio 2: 1.2: 1; r–m at basal 0.65 of discal cell. Halter pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">Abdomen yellowish brown with gray microtomentum except for yellow two sides and basal portions of tergites 2–5 with 2 brown small spots; venter yellow. Setulae on abdomen black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[394,527,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[326,1258,205,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[313,1273,193,1556]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Lasiosina recurvata sp. n., male. 9 male terminalia, posterior view; 10 male terminalia, lateral view; 11 hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view; 12 hypandrium and phallic complex, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263252/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">Figs. 9–12</figureCitation>
): Epandrium brown with long brown setulae, inner posteroventral magins approximated; surstylus long, broad, parallel–sided, with small spinous processes, 0.5x as high as epandrium in latral view. Cercus small, triangular in ventral view, with 1 pair of setulae. Gonites arranged in a row; postgonite 0.5x as long as pregonite, postgonite slightly recurved distally with pointed apex, with some sensory setulae, gradually narrowed basally; pregonite narrowed basally, flat distally; distiphallus and basiphallus short; phallapodeme long, beyond basal margin of hypandrium with basal stalk broad in lateral view. Hypandrium narrowed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,896]" box="[199,414,764,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="386">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
